    <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X:{A}\downarrow {\mathcal {U}}]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="/jms-003O/" title="Reflection algebras and homomorphisms" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-003O/" display-uri="jms-003O" type="local">reflection algebra</fr:link>; we define the identity homomorphism <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[1_{X}:X\multimap  X]]></fr:tex> on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> as follows:</html:p>
    <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[  \begin {array}{l}
  1_{X}x :\equiv  x \\
  \eta _{1_{X}} a :\equiv  \mathsf {refl}
\end {array}
]]></fr:tex>
    <html:p>Now let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[Y,Z:{A}\downarrow {\mathcal {U}}]]></fr:tex> be two further <fr:link href="/jms-003O/" title="Reflection algebras and homomorphisms" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-003O/" display-uri="jms-003O" type="local">reflection algebras</fr:link> and let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f : X\multimap  Y]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g : Y\multimap  Z]]></fr:tex> be two <fr:link href="/jms-003O/" title="Reflection algebras and homomorphisms" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-003O/" display-uri="jms-003O" type="local">homomorphisms of reflection algebras</fr:link>. The composite homomorphism <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f;g : X\multimap  Z]]></fr:tex> is defined like so:</html:p>
    <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[  \begin {array}{l}
  {\mathopen {}\left (f;g\right )\mathclose {}}x :\equiv  g{\mathopen {}\left (fx\right )\mathclose {}} \\
  \eta _{f;g}a :\equiv  \mathsf {ap}_{g}\,{\mathopen {}\left (\eta _{f}a\right )\mathclose {}}\bullet  \eta _{g}a
\end {array}
]]></fr:tex>
  </fr:mainmatter>
