                <fr:title text="Homotopies between reflection algebra homomorphisms">Homotopies between reflection algebra homomorphisms</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>Given a pair of <fr:link href="/jms-003O/" title="Reflection algebras and homomorphisms" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-003O/" display-uri="jms-003O" type="local">reflection algebras</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X,Y:{\mathcal {U}}\downarrow {A}]]></fr:tex> and a pair of <fr:link href="/jms-003O/" title="Reflection algebras and homomorphisms" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-003O/" display-uri="jms-003O" type="local">homomorphisms</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f,g : X\multimap  Y]]></fr:tex>, a <html:em>homotopy</html:em> from <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g]]></fr:tex> is defined to be a homotopy <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\phi  : {Uf} \sim _{X\to  Y} {Ug}]]></fr:tex> between the underlying functions together with a witness <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\bar {\phi }]]></fr:tex>  of the following coherence:</html:p>
                <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[   \bar \phi  :
\mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{{\mathopen {}\left (a:A\right )\mathclose {}}}}{\textstyle \prod _{{\mathopen {}\left (a:A\right )\mathclose {}}}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{{\mathopen {}\left (a:A\right )\mathclose {}}}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{{\mathopen {}\left (a:A\right )\mathclose {}}}}
{
  \eta _{g}a
} =_{
  {g{\mathopen {}\left (\eta _{X}a\right )\mathclose {}}} =_{Y} {\eta _{Y}a}
} {
  \eta _{f}a\bullet  \phi {\mathopen {}\left (\eta _{X}a\right )\mathclose {}}
