                <fr:title text="Path spaces of algebra homomorphisms">Path spaces of algebra homomorphisms</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Lemma</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>Given a path of <fr:link href="/jms-003O/" title="Reflection algebras and homomorphisms" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-003O/" display-uri="jms-003O" type="local">reflection algebras</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X,Y:{A}\downarrow {\mathcal {U}}]]></fr:tex> and a <fr:link href="/jms-003O/" title="Reflection algebras and homomorphisms" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-003O/" display-uri="jms-003O" type="local">homomorphism</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f : X\multimap  Y]]></fr:tex>, the type <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathchoice {\textstyle \sum _{{\mathopen {}\left (g:X\multimap  Y\right )\mathclose {}}}}{\textstyle \sum _{{\mathopen {}\left (g:X\multimap  Y\right )\mathclose {}}}}{\scriptstyle \sum _{{\mathopen {}\left (g:X\multimap  Y\right )\mathclose {}}}}{\scriptscriptstyle \sum _{{\mathopen {}\left (g:X\multimap  Y\right )\mathclose {}}}}{{g} \sim _{X\multimap  Y} {f}}]]></fr:tex> of homomorphisms equipped with a <fr:link href="/jms-003X/" title="Homotopies between reflection algebra homomorphisms" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-003X/" display-uri="jms-003X" type="local">homotopy</fr:link> to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is contractible, by function extensionality and the characterization of path spaces in dependent sums. Hence it follows that the canonical map <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{f} =_{X\multimap  Y} {g}\to  {f} \sim _{X\multimap  Y} {g}]]></fr:tex> is an equivalence.</html:p>
