                <fr:title text="Displayed reflection algebras over displayed reflection algebras">Displayed reflection algebras over displayed reflection algebras</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[Y]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link href="/jms-003R/" title="Displayed reflection algebra" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-003R/" display-uri="jms-003R" type="local">displayed reflection algebra</fr:link> over a <fr:link href="/jms-003O/" title="Reflection algebras and homomorphisms" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-003O/" display-uri="jms-003O" type="local">reflection algebra</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X:{A}\downarrow {\mathcal {U}}]]></fr:tex>, we define a <html:em>displayed reflection algebra over <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[Y]]></fr:tex></html:em> to be a <fr:link href="/jms-003R/" title="Displayed reflection algebra" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-003R/" display-uri="jms-003R" type="local">displayed reflection algebra</fr:link> in the original sense over the <fr:link href="/jms-003S/" title="The total reflection algebra" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-003S/" display-uri="jms-003S" type="local">total reflection algebra</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\widetilde {Y}]]></fr:tex> corresponding to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[Y]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
